#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:31
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Although it is theoretically possible to use a full disk to house your Linux\n"
"system, this is almost never done in practice. Instead, full disk block devices\n"
"are split up in smaller, more manageable block devices. On <keyval id=\"arch\"/>\n"
"systems, these are called <e>partitions</e>. There are currently two standard\n"
"partitioning technologies in use: MBR and GPT.\n"
msgstr "Linuxシステムを格納するのにディスクの全体を使用することは理論上可能ですが、実際にはほとんどそうはされません。代わりにディスク全体のブロックデバイスはもっと扱いやすいブロックデバイスにより小さく分割されます。<keyval id=\"arch\"/>システムではこれら分割されたものを<e>パーティション</e>と呼びます。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:39
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <e>MBR (Master Boot Record)</e> setup uses 32-bit identifiers for\n"
"partitions, and supports three partition types: <e>primary</e>, \n"
"<e>extended</e> and <e>logical</e>. Primary partitions have their information\n"
"stored in the master boot record itself - a very small (usually 512 bytes)\n"
"location at the very beginning of a disk. Due to this small space, only four\n"
"primary partitions are supported (for instance, <path>/dev/sda1</path> to\n"
"<path>/dev/sda4</path>).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:49
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To support more partitions, one of the primary partitions can be marked as an\n"
"extended partition. This partition can then contain logical partitions\n"
"(partitions within a partition).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:55
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Each partition is limited to 2 TB in size (due to the 32-bit identifiers).\n"
"Also, the MBR setup does not provide any backup-MBR, so if an application\n"
"or user overwrites the MBR, all partition information is lost.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:62
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <e>GPT (GUID Partition table)</e> setup uses 64-bit identifiers for\n"
"the partitions. The location in which it stores the partition information\n"
"is also much bigger than the 512 bytes of an MBR, and there is no limit on\n"
"the amount of partitions. Also the size of a partition is bounded by a much\n"
"greater limit (almost 8 ZB - yes, zettabytes).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:70
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When a system's software interface between the operating system and firmware\n"
"is UEFI (instead of BIOS), GPT is almost mandatory as compatibility issues will\n"
"arise with MBR here.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"GPT also has the advantage that it has a backup GPT at the end of the disk,\n"
"which can be used to recover damage of the primary GPT at the beginning. GPT\n"
"also carries CRC32 checksums to detect errors in the header and partition\n"
"tables.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "So, GPT or MBR?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:89
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"From the description above, one might think that using GPT should always be the\n"
"recommended approach. But there are a few caveats with this.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Using GPT on a BIOS-based computer works, but you cannot dual-boot then with a\n"
"Microsoft Windows operating system. The reason is that Microsoft Windows will\n"
"boot in EFI mode if it detects a GPT partition label.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Some buggy BIOSes or EFIs configured to boot in BIOS/CSM/legacy mode might also\n"
"have problems with booting from GPT labeled disks. If that is the case, you \n"
"might be able to work around the problem by adding the boot/active flag on the\n"
"protective MBR partition which has to be done through <c>fdisk</c>\n"
"(<c>parted</c> understands the GPT tables and would not show the protective\n"
"MBR partition):\n"
msgstr ""

