#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:196
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The number of partitions is highly dependent on your environment. For instance,\n"
"if you have lots of users, you will most likely want to have your\n"
"<path>/home</path> separate as it increases security and makes backups easier.\n"
"If you are installing Gentoo to perform as a mailserver, your \n"
"<path>/var</path> should be separate as all mails are stored inside \n"
"<path>/var</path>. A good choice of filesystem will then maximise your \n"
"performance. Gameservers will have a separate <path>/opt</path> as most gaming \n"
"servers are installed there. The reason is similar for <path>/home</path>: \n"
"security and backups. You will definitely want to keep <path>/usr</path> big:\n"
"not only will it contain the majority of applications, the Portage tree alone\n"
"takes around 500 Mbyte excluding the various sources that are stored in it.\n"
msgstr "パーティションの数は環境に大きく依存します。例えば、多数のユーザーがいるのならセキュリテイを強めバックアップを容易にする為に多分<path>/home</path>を別にしたいでしょう。もしメールサーバーとして稼働させる為にGentooをインストールしようとしているのなら、全てのメールは <path>/var</path>内に保存されるので<path>/var</path>は別にすべきでしょう。ファイルシステムの良い選択はパフォーマンスを最大限にするでしょう。ゲームサーバーではほとんどのゲームサーバーパッケージが<path>/opt</path>にインストールされるので、そこは別にされます。理由は<path>/home</path>をセキュリティとバックアップの為に別にするのと同じようなものです。<path>/usr</path>は絶対に大きく取らなければならないです。大部分のアプリケーションが含まれるだけでなく、Portageツリーだけで、保存されるソースは別にしても500MB程度は取られます。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:210
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As you can see, it very much depends on what you want to achieve. Separate\n"
"partitions or volumes have the following advantages:\n"
msgstr "こういったように、どういうシステムにしたいのかにかなり依存します。分割されたパーティションまたはボリュームには以下の利点があります。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:216
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "  You can choose the best performing filesystem for each partition or volume\n"
msgstr "  それぞれのパーティションまたはボリュームに最適なパフォーマンスを上げるファイルシステムを選択できます。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:219
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  Your entire system cannot run out of free space if one defunct tool is\n"
"  continuously writing files to a partition or volume\n"
msgstr "  パーティションを分けておくと、あるゾンビプロセスがパーティションまたはボリュームにデータを書き込み続けてシステム全体の空き容量を使い果たすのを防ぐことができます。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:223
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  If necessary, file system checks are reduced in time, as multiple checks can\n"
"  be done in parallel (although this advantage is more with multiple disks than\n"
"  it is with multiple partitions)\n"
msgstr "  必要ならば、並行した複数のチェックを行えるのでファイルシステムのチェック時間を減らせます。(この利点は複数のパーティションでよりも複数のディスクでより有効ですが)。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:228
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  Security can be enhanced by mounting some partitions or volumes read-only, \n"
"  nosuid (setuid bits are ignored), noexec (executable bits are ignored) etc.\n"
msgstr " セキュリティは読込専用、nosuid(setuidビットは無視されます)、noexec(実行ビットは無視されます)等でいくつかのパーティションをマウントすることで増大します。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:234
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"However, multiple partitions have disadvantages as well. If not configured\n"
"properly, you will have a system with lots of free space on one partition and\n"
"none on another. Another nuisance is that separate partitions - especially\n"
"for important mountpoints like <path>/usr</path> or <path>/var</path> - often\n"
"require the administrator to boot with an initramfs to mount the partition\n"
"before other boot scripts start. This isn't always the case though, so your\n"
"results may vary.\n"
msgstr ""
"しかし、複数のパーティションにもいくつか欠点があります。\n"
"正しく設定しないと、空き容量がかなりあるパーティションと空き容量の無いパーティションのあるシステムになってしまうでしょう。\n"
"もうひとつやっかいなのはパーティション(特に<path>/usr</path>や<path>/var</path>といった大切なもの)が分かれていると、\n"
"initramfsを使ってブートスクリプトが実行される前に、パーティションをマウントするように設定しなければいけない、ということもあります。\n"
"とはいえ、これはどんな環境でも問題になるというわけではありません。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:244
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There is also a 15-partition limit for SCSI and SATA unless you use GPT\n"
"labels.\n"
msgstr "また、SCSIとSATAではGPTラベルを使わなければ15個迄というパーティション数の制限があります。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:251
#, no-wrap
msgid "What about swap space?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:255
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There is no perfect value for the swap partition. The purpose of swap space is\n"
"to provide disk storage to the kernel when internal memory (RAM) is under\n"
"pressure. A swap space allows for the kernel to move memory pages that are\n"
"not likely to be accessed soon to disk (swap or page-out), freeing memory. Of\n"
"course, if that memory is suddenly needed, these pages need to be put back in\n"
"memory (page-in) which will take a while (as disks are very slow compared to\n"
"internal memory).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:265
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are not going to run memory intensive applications or you have lots of\n"
"memory available, then you probably do not need much swap space. However, swap\n"
"space is also used to store the entire memory in case of hibernation. If you\n"
"plan on using hibernation, you will need a bigger swap space, often at least\n"
"the amount of memory you have in your system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:275
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "What is the BIOS boot partition?"
msgstr "ブートパーティションを作成する"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:279
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A BIOS boot partition is a very small (1 to 2 MB) partition in which\n"
"bootloaders like GRUB2 can put additional data that doesn't fit in the\n"
"allocated storage (a few hundred bytes in case of MBR) and cannot place\n"
"elsewhere.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:286
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Such partitions are not always necessary, but considering the low space\n"
"consumption and the difficulties we would have with documenting the plethora\n"
"of partitioning differences otherwise, it is recommended to create it in\n"
"either case.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:293
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For completeness, we can say that the BIOS boot partition is needed when\n"
"GPT partition layout is used with GRUB2, or when the MBR partition layout\n"
"is used with GRUB2 when the first partition starts earlier than the 1 MB\n"
"location on the disk.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:303
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Default: Using parted to Partition your Disk"
msgstr "パーティション作成にpartedを使う"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:308
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In this chapter, we guide you through the creation of the example partition\n"
"layout mentioned earlier in the instructions, but repeat here again for\n"
"your convenience:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:337
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:564
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Change your partition layout according to your own preference.\n"
msgstr "パーティションの割当てを自分の望むように変更してください。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:343
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:570
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing the Current Partition Layout"
msgstr "現在のパーティションの割当てを見る"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:347
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>parted</c> application offers a simple interface for partitioning your\n"
"disks and supports very large partitions (more than 2 TB). Fire up\n"
"<c>parted</c> on your disk (in our example, we use <path>/dev/sda</path>).\n"
"We will ask <c>parted</c> to use optimum alignment:\n"
msgstr ""
"<c>parted</c>は<c>fdisk</c>をいくらか新しくモダンにしたようなものです。\n"
"ディスクのパーティション設定を行なう簡潔なメニューを持ち、\n"
"非常に大きなパーティション(2TB以上)をサポートしています。\n"
"では、<c>parted</c>を起動してディスクのパーティションを設定しましょう。\n"
"(この例では<path>/dev/sda</path>を使います。)\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:353
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Starting parted"
msgstr "partedの起動"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:354
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>parted -a optimal /dev/sda</i>\n"
"GNU Parted 2.3\n"
"Using /dev/sda\n"
"Welcome to GNU Parted! Type 'help' to view a list of commands.\n"
msgstr ""
"# <i>parted /dev/sda</i>\n"
"GNU Parted 2.3\n"
"Using /dev/vda\n"
"Welcome to GNU Parted! Type 'help' to view a list of commands.\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:361
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Alignment means that partitions are started on well-known boundaries within\n"
"the disk, ensuring that operations on the disk from the operating system level\n"
"(retrieve pages from the disk) use the least amount of internal disk\n"
"operations. Misaligned partitions might require the disk to fetch two pages\n"
"instead of one even if the operating system asked for a single page.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:369
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To find out about all options supported by <c>parted</c>, type <c>help</c> and\n"
"press return.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:376
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Setting the GPT Label"
msgstr "GPTラベルの設定"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:380
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Most disks on x86/amd64 are prepared using an <e>msdos</e> label. Using\n"
"<c>parted</c>, we can put a GPT label on the disk using <c>mklabel gpt</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><warn>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:385
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Changing the partition type will remove all partitions from your disk. All data\n"
"on the disk will be lost.\n"
msgstr ""
"パーティションタイプを変更すると全てのパーティションがディスクから削除されます。\n"
"ディスク上の全てのデータが失われます。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:389
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Setting the GPT label"
msgstr "GPTラベルの設定"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:390
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "(parted) <i>mklabel gpt</i>\n"
msgstr "(parted) <i>mklabel gpt</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:394
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you want the disk to have MBR layout, use <c>mklabel msdos</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:400
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:624
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Removing all Partitions"
msgstr "全てのパーティションを削除する"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:404
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If this isn't done yet (for instance through the <c>mklabel</c> operation\n"
"earlier, or because the disk is a freshly formatted one), we will first\n"
"remove all existing partitions from the disk. Type <c>print</c> to view the\n"
"current partitions, and <c>rm &lt;number&gt;</c> where &lt;number&gt; is the\n"
"partition you want to remove.\n"
msgstr ""
"まだパーティションが(たとえば<c>mklabel</c>を事前にやっていたり、\n"
"ディスクが新しく一からフォーマットされたものであるなどによって)全て削除されていなければ、\n"
"最初に現在の全てのパーティションをディスクから削除します。\n"
"<c>rm &lt;number&gt;</c>とします。&lt;number&gt;は削除したいパーティションの番号です。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:411
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Removing a partition from the disk"
msgstr "パーティションを削除する"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:412
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "(parted) <i>rm 2</i>\n"
msgstr "(parted) <i>rm 2</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:416
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Do the same for all other partitions that you don't need. However, make sure you\n"
"do not make any mistakes here - <c>parted</c> executes the changes immediately\n"
"(unlike <c>fdisk</c> which stages them, allowing a user to \"undo\" his changes\n"
"before saving or exiting <c>fdisk</c>).\n"
msgstr ""
"同様にして必要ない全てのパーティションを削除してください。しかし、ミスをしないように気をつけてください!\n"
"<c>parted</c>は変更をただちにディスクに反映します。(変更内容だけを記憶し、実際に保存したり終了したりする前に変更内容を「戻す」ことができる<c>fdisk</c>とは違う、というわけです)\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:425
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the Partitions"
msgstr "パーティションを作成するa"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:429
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now let's create the partitions we mentioned earlier. Creating partitions with\n"
"<c>parted</c> isn't very difficult - all we need to do is inform <c>parted</c>\n"
"about the following settings:\n"
msgstr ""
"それでは先ほど述べたパーティションを作成していきましょう。\n"
"<c>parted</c>でのパーティション作成はそんなに難しくはありません。\n"
"以下の項目を<c>parted</c>に教えるだけです。\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:436
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The <e>partition type</e> to use. This usually is <e>primary</e>.\n"
"    If you use the <e>msdos</e> partition label, keep in mind that you can have\n"
"    no more than 4 primary partitions. If you need more than 4 partitions, make\n"
"    a partition <e>extended</e> and create <e>logical</e> partitions inside it.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:442
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The start location of a partition (which can be expressed in MB, GB, ...)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    パーティションの開始位置(MBまたはGBで指定できます)\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:445
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The end location of the partition (which can be expressed in MB, GB, ...)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    パーティションの終了位置(MBまたはGBで指定できます)\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:450
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, we tell <c>parted</c> that the size unit we work with is megabytes\n"
"(actually mebibytes, abbreviated as MiB which is the \"standard\" notation, but\n"
"we will use MB in the text throughout as it is much more common):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:455
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using MiB units"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:456
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "(parted) <i>unit mib</i>\n"
msgstr "(parted) <i>rm 2</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/hb-install-x86+amd64-disk.xml:460
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now create a 2 MB partition that will be used by the GRUB2 bootloader later.\n"
"We use the <c>mkpart</c> command for this, and inform <c>parted</c> to start\n"
"from 1 MB and end at 3 MB (creating a partition of 2 MB in size).\n"
